reason.tex:
%text The notation used to express conditional probability has a very special -- and a very precise -- meaning.
The table below should help you remember \underline\text{when to use which notation}
%
\begin{tabular}{|c|c|c|} \hline \text{Notation} & \text{What you know} & \text{Probability to find} \\ \hline P\left( A\,\vert\, B\right) & \text{B has happened} & \text{$A$ happened?}\\ \hline P\left( B\,\vert\, A\right) & \text{A has happened} & \text{$B$ happened?}\\ \hline P\left(A\cap B\right) & \text{Nothing} & \text{$A$ and $B$ } \\ & & \text{happening together} \\ \hline \end{tabular}
